Here are both approaches for Shell navigation in .NET MAUI:

**1. Passing the product ID (string parameter):**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?ProductId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full Product object (complex parameter):**

```csharp
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "Product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
}
```

**Receiving data with `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("ProductId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from service if needed
            _ = LoadProductAsync(ProductId);
        }

        // Approach 2: complex object
        if (query.TryGetValue("Product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadProductAsync(string id)
    {
        Product = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(id);
    }
}
```

**Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|--|--|--|
| Syntax | Query string `?key=val` | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| Survives serialization | Yes (URL-safe) | No (transient, in-memory only) |
| Use when | Deep links, simple IDs | You already have the object loaded |

The string approach is preferred for deep-link support; the object approach avoids redundant data fetching when you already have the model in memory.
